🇮🇳 Starlink signs agreement with Indian telecom providers
</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">After years of delays, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-15-03-2025-wn2-4-starlink-may-finally-enter-india" target="_blank">Starlink may finally enter India</a> following a meeting between PM Narendra Modi and Elon Musk. Despite previously opposing Starlink, telecom duopoly Airtel and Jio have now signed an agreement with SpaceX to distribute its satellite internet services in India.
</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">However, government clearance is still pending, with concerns about security and regulatory approvals. Indian government retains the right to intercept all telecom frequencies to fight terrorism</p>
