          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
            Dubai’s property market is booming, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-15-03-2025-wn3-5-with-price-rising-147-percent?source=website" target="_blank">with prices rising 147%</a> in five years and residential sales hitting $32.7 billion in Q3 2024. The Golden Visa program has attracted wealthy buyers from Europe and North America, increasing long-term residency. Developers are shifting focus toward family-friendly homes and larger apartments, moving away from speculative investments.
            </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Neighboring Abu Dhabi is adopting a more measured approach. It plans to leverage its $1.7 Tn sovereign wealth fund to focus on luxury, cultural, and family-oriented living. Bahrain is modernizing while preserving its historical architecture. Ras Al Khaimah is emerging as a new luxury destination, with 60+ high-end projects and the UAE’s first casino resort opening by 2027.</p>
