        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/new-funds-flow-into-real-estate-asset-classes-europe.jpg" alt="New funds flow into different real estate asset classes in Europe" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
             <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>New funds flow into different real estate asset classes in Europe.</i></p> 
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Rising interest rates:</strong> New banking rules (CRR III in 2025) will require closer monitoring of real estate loan portfolios, increasing pressure on banks and borrowers. With falling property values, many borrowers may struggle to refinance loans, leading to potential defaults or distressed sales.</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Economic slowdown:</strong> Weak economic growth and recession fears make investors hesitant to commit to long-term real estate assets. 63% of assets transacted <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-15-03-2025-pt1-6-since-2017-have-lost-value?source=website" target="_blank">since 2017 have lost value</a> over the last two years (Q2 2022 to Q2 2024), especially in the office sector.</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Declining office demand:</strong> The shift to remote and hybrid work has reduced the need for office spaces, lowering office investment volumes. 95% of UK office and 74% of UK retail properties have fallen in value, with tightening lending conditions making refinancing harder.</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Struggling retail sector:</strong> Growth in e-commerce and dark stores and warehouses, along with changing consumer habits, have led to lower demand for physical retail spaces. Cities like Madrid have experienced retail price drops of 40.7% since 2017.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Stricter ESG regulations:</strong> Governments are tightening sustainability rules, forcing investors to spend more on upgrades and reducing profitability.</p>


        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
